This Week with R-O-M

I count 347 Rules in the latest Rule set.  Here are the five random selections:

  6 = Rule  754 Spelling and Grammar Errors
135 = Rule 1796 Validity of Orders
196 = Rule 1814 Timing of Penalties for Crimes and Infractions
236 = Rule 1730 Delayed Transfer Orders
207 = Rule 1691 Category of New Rules

I have always tried to honor them in the past, but Delayed Transfer Orders are
actually something of a pain.  The only other reference to them in the Rules is
in Happy Birthday and I will add a provision to this proposal to clean that up
too.  So, I hereby select Rule 1730 for the R-O-M this week.

Acting as Executor and on behalf of the Repeal-O-Matic, I hereby submit the
following proposal and pay one P-Note from the R-O-M to the Bank to increase
its priority by one:

PROPOSAL: Repeal Rule 1730 (Delayed Transfer Orders)
This Proposal shall have an AI = 1

Rule 1730 is hereby Repealed.

Rule 1727 is amended by replacing the text

      BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that, not less than seven days prior to
      Agora's Birthday, the Chancellor shall, on behalf of the Bank,
      submit delayed Transfer Orders to be executed at 00:04:30 GMT
      +1200 on Agora's Birthday to each Player for the amount of 3 VTs
      each;

with the text

      BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that, as soon as possible after Agora's
      Birthday, the Chancellor shall, on behalf of the Bank, submit
      Transfer Orders to each Player for the amount of 3 VTs each;

===========

-- Promotor Crito


